The Yellowhead Chiefs scored twice in 38 seconds in the third period as they beat the Brandon Midget AAA Wheat Kings 3-1 on Friday at the Sportsplex. 
Dayton Heino scored a power-play goal 13 minutes into the final frame and Ryan Heino scored shortly after as the Chiefs improved to 4-2-0-2 and currently sit in fourth place in the Manitoba AAA Midget Hockey League. Please subscribe to view full article.
